This paper discusses the implementation and modeling of software-defined networks in vehicular networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). It also discusses the use of LTE-V2X communications, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also touches upon security issues in vehicular networks, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). The use of software-defined networks in intelligent transportation systems also relates to control systems (cs.SY). Lastly, the paper discusses the challenges faced by vehicular ad-hoc networks, which is related to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
